⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Fred Skolnik
node CPS · CPS · ⟦Fred Skolnik:CPS:9f5419⟧

WHO   — Fred Skolnik — the stepfather · the abuser, the victim
WHAT  — The transposed ‘victim’: not the novel's miserly pawnbroker but an abuser, which is what makes the film's killing sympathetic where the novel's is monstrous.
WHERE — CPS · Crime + Punishment in Suburbia  Framework inputs: Crime + Punishment in Suburbia (2000)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because moving the victim from a harmless old woman to an abuser is the single choice that re-weights the whole moral question.
HOW   — By drink, cruelty, and an assault that pushes Roseanne and Jimmy to murder.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the reason she killed — which is exactly why this isn't Dostoevsky: his victim was harmless, and mine made the axe feel like mercy.

